    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>pasta </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked pasta</strong>, reserving a large cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Whilst the pasta is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>salmon fillet[s] </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until browned on both sides and almost cooked through</p><p>Once browned, transfer to a plate and set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>to the pan and stir until the sauce begins to thicken</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove and discard the skin from the <strong>salmon</strong></p><p>Raise the heat to medium-high, then flake the<strong> salmon</strong> into the pan, then cook for 3-4 min or until the salmon is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked through when it's opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the salmon is cooked, remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>pasta </strong>with your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong>, <strong>wilted spinach </strong>and the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon[s]</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a generous grind of<strong> pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up until the pasta is fully coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy salmon & spinach pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the<strong> </strong>starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-salmon-and-spinach-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Serve the<strong> creamy salmon & spinach tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped chives</strong> and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
